The paper deals with image translation, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a generator and an adversarial term suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a new model for image translation, which involves learning to attend to key parts of the image, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of attention maps, which are commonly used in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
